OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1784031511
OL,3,CMasts of Second World War shipwreck to
OL,4,Cbe cut down in September
OL,6,FExperts believe reducing the masts'
OL,7,Fheight to below sea level will ease
OL,8,Fpressure on the wreck's structure and
OL,9,Freduce the risk of heavy objects
OL,10,Ffalling onto the munitions below.
OL,12,FThe masts will be taken to Chatham's
OL,13,FHistoric Dockyard for preservation and
OL,14,Fdisplay.
OL,16,FMaritime minister Keir Mather said
OL,17,Fthat, after preservation work, teams
OL,18,Fdismantling the masts will "be able to
OL,19,Fmake a decision about where they are
OL,20,Fbest placed, so that local communities
OL,21,Fcan access them".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1784031511
OL,3,CMasts of Second World War shipwreck to
OL,4,Cbe cut down in September
OL,6,FAn "exclusion zone will remain in
OL,7,Fplace for as long as it needs to"
OL,8,Faround the vessel, but the "wreck
OL,9,Fitself is stable", he added.
OL,11,FRobin Rickard, who is providing
OL,12,Fstrategic explosive ordnance advice to
OL,13,Fthe Department for Transport (DfT),
OL,14,Fsaid work to remove the masts would
OL,15,Frequire a jackup barge - a floating
OL,16,Fplatform on long legs "firmly anchored
OL,17,Finto the seabed, so it won't move".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1784031511
OL,3,CMasts of Second World War shipwreck to
OL,4,Cbe cut down in September
OL,6,FHe added: "We're going to put a jackup
OL,7,Fbarge alongside it, both the stern
OL,8,Fsection and the forward section, and
OL,9,Fthen we're going to use a diamond wire
OL,10,Fsaw to chop the masts and recover
OL,11,Fthem."
OL,13,FSS Richard Montgomery - or 'Monty' -
OL,14,Fwas carrying "safe-to-transport
OL,15,Fmunitions" during its doomed voyage
OL,16,Ffrom the United States to Great
OL,17,FBritain, Mr Rickard said.
OL,19,F"So specifically, they were't armed or
OL,20,Ffused during transport," he added.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1784031511
OL,3,CMasts of Second World War shipwreck to
OL,4,Cbe cut down in September
OL,6,F"So, I'm not surprised that they've
OL,7,Fbeen sat in wet storage for 82 years
OL,8,Fand nothing's happened, which is good
OL,9,Fnews."
OL,11,FPaul Barnard, the deputy chief
OL,12,Fexecutive at Chatham Historic Dockyard
OL,13,FTrust, said the vessel served as a
OL,14,F"permanent reminder of the Second
OL,15,FWorld War, the role that not just the
OL,16,FNavy allied forces played but also
OL,17,Fthose support-class vessels".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1784031511
OL,3,CMasts of Second World War shipwreck to
OL,4,Cbe cut down in September
OL,6,FHe said the masts, which have towered
OL,7,Fabove the water's surface, "are a
OL,8,Freally really important part of the
OL,9,Fship and they're an important part of
OL,10,Fthe story".
OL,12,FTo keep the ship's masts in the UK,
OL,13,Fteams from the DfT have had to speak
OL,14,Fwith their counterparts in Washington.
OL,16,FUS ambassador to the UK Warren
OL,17,FStephens last month wrote to Kevin
OL,18,FMcKenna, the Labour MP for
OL,19,FSittingbourne and Sheppey, telling him
OL,20,Fhe backed efforts to display the masts.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
